Japanese Bought Net 388.1 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-03-24T23:54:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/japanese-bought-net-388-1-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended March 18 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 388.1 billion yen ($4.8 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 101.7 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 4.1 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 290.5 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 190.4 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 891 billion yen in stocks, and sold 895.5 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 186
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  